Ticket 1 — Network Connectivity Issue
User: Sarah M.
Department: Finance
Issue: “I can’t access any websites. Teams works but nothing loads in Chrome.”

🔍 Technician Notes
Verified user is connected to Wi‑Fi

Teams functioning suggests partial connectivity

Browser unable to resolve domains

🧪 Troubleshooting Steps
DNS Resolution test using Resolve-DnsName

Ping Tests to 8.8.8.8 and microsoft.com

Proxy Settings checked via netsh winhttp show proxy

Cleared Chrome cache

Flushed DNS: ipconfig /flushdns

✅ Resolution
DNS client service was stopped. Restarted:

Code
net stop dnscache
net start dnscache
Browser immediately began resolving domains.

📌 Preventative Recommendation
Add DNS Client service to monitoring list.
